TESS Program Academic Research Data

Contains information about 221 research projects funded by the TESS program (Time-Sharing Experiments in the Social Sciences).

filedrawer

Format

A data frame with 221 rows and 5 variables:

id
integer: study identifier
journal
character: discipline of the journal for published articles
DV
character: publication status
IV
character: statistical significance of the main findings
max.h
integer: H-index (highest among authors)

Details

See QSS Table 7.5.

  • Annie Franco, Neil Malhotra, and Gabor Simonovits (2014) “Publication bias in the social sciences: Unlocking the file drawer.” Science, vol. 345, no. 6203, pp. 1502–1505. doi = 10.1126/science.1255484
  • Annie Franco, Neil Malhotra, and Gabor Simonovits (2015) “Underreporting in political science survey experiments: Comparing questionnaires to published results.” Political Analysis, vol. 23, pp. 206–312. doi = 10.1093/pan/mpv006
